      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>https://localhost:1313/wiaposts/the-way-of-mother/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://localhost:1313/assets/images/wiapost/5016-The-Way-Of-Mother.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;The Way Of Mother&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;The Way Of Mother 
    &lt;div id=&#34;the-way-of-mother&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#the-way-of-mother&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A twelve years old boy in a deep mountain  &lt;br&gt;
quite engrossed in his play with crops, trees, mud, cattle, and fountain.  &lt;br&gt;
He had a mother and other siblings  &lt;br&gt;
His mother used to scold him and sometimes beat him for his mischief.  &lt;br&gt;
Boy was very angry and questioned why my mother is unfair to me.  &lt;br&gt;
One day he asked his mother. Are you my real mother?  &lt;br&gt;
Why do you beat me and not my other siblings?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
